{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-16T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On 17 April, International Bat Appreciation Day flips its cape to the planet's night shift: bats. With more than 1,400 species on every continent except Antarctica, these winged mammals keep ecosystems balanced. They've been on Earth for over 50 million years, and only three species are true vampires. Found only in the Americas, these bats feed on blood, while the rest survive on insects, fruit, nectar or pollen. In Texas, Bracken Cave can host up to 20 million Mexican free-tailed bats in summer. Many gulp crop pests, cutting pesticide use; others pollinate wild agaves and disperse seeds that help forests rebound.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-GB2090404206_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-GB2090404206_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bat signal: ON","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-37.798065,145.012222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-37.798065,145.012222;S9;Yarra Bend Park, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bats&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"2090404206","FullDateString":"17 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Washington's Skagit Valley transforms into a patchwork of colour as the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors can explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-GB8838173363_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-GB8838173363_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Petal parade","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.5,-122.033/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.5,-122.033;S9;Skagit Valley, Washington, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260415_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"8838173363","FullDateString":"16 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Art surrounds us. Creativity and self-expression are part of human identity and mould our past and future. While some might dedicate their lives to the arts, others are the recipients of what artists channel. World Art Day on April 15 celebrates this ever-flowing link between artistic creations and society that shapes our cultures.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-GB8594559434_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-GB8594559434_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Stepping inside the living canvas","Title":"The Carrières des Lumières exhibit of Vincent van Gogh, Les Baux-de-Provence, France","Copyright":"© Patrick Aventurier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"World Art Day is held on 15 April to mark the birthday of Leonardo da Vinci, honouring his lasting influence on art and human creativity.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Art+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260414_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields"},"Ssd":"20260415","Name":"VanGoghFields","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"8594559434","FullDateString":"15 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Sea anemones may look like underwater flowers, but they're actually animals—close relatives of jellyfish and corals. Anchored to rocks or reefs, they use a sticky base and a crown of waving tentacles armed with tiny stingers to capture passing prey. Those stings can paralyse small fish, yet one famous neighbour is immune.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_EN-GB8330340192_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_EN-GB8330340192_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Reefside roommates","Title":"Common clownfish in a sea anemone, Raja Ampat Islands, Indonesia","Copyright":"© Magnus Lundgren/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.233312,130.507889/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.233312,130.507889;S9;Raja Ampat Islands, Southwest Papua, Indonesia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sea+anemone&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260413_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish"},"Ssd":"20260414","Name":"OcellarisClownfish","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"8330340192","FullDateString":"14 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the lights go down, the universe puts on a show. International Dark Sky Week, celebrated each April, invites everyone to rediscover the night and learn why darkness is worth protecting. Launched in 2003, the week highlights how excessive artificial light affects wildlife, human health, energy use and our ability to see the stars. Fewer lights don't mean less safety—smart, well-designed lighting can do both.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_EN-GB8139506405_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_EN-GB8139506405_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"After the lights go down","Title":"Milky Way over Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, California, United States","Copyright":"© Kevin Key/Slworking)/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.100494,-116.301331/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.100494,-116.301331;S9;Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, Borrego Springs, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Dark+Sky+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260412_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars"},"Ssd":"20260413","Name":"BorregoStars","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"8139506405","FullDateString":"13 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, the world marks the International Day of Human Space Flight, a United Nations observance honouring the first human journey into space and the start of the space age for humanity. The date recalls 12 April, 1961, when Yuri Gagarin orbited Earth, proving that people could leave the planet and return safely.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_EN-GB7928814675_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_EN-GB7928814675_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The first step off Earth","Title":"City lights streak below, taken from the International Space Station","Copyright":"© NASA","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The UN established the International Day of Human Space Flight in 2011, 50 years after the first human spaceflight.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+of+Human+Space+Flight&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260411_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails"},"Ssd":"20260412","Name":"SpaceTrails","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"7928814675","FullDateString":"12 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A beach born from fire rarely does so subtly, yet Papagayo Beach manages exactly that. The shoreline we see today rests on the southern edge of Lanzarote, one of Spain's Canary Islands. Tropical fantasy? More like volcanic precision. Millions of years ago, this land rose in successive layers of basalt and ash thrust upward by submarine eruptions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_EN-GB7620407286_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_EN-GB7620407286_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Volcanic veneer","Title":"Papagayo Beach, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/28.84295,-13.78824/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=28.84295,-13.78824;S9;Playa del Papagayo, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lanzarote+Canary+Islands+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260410_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo"},"Ssd":"20260411","Name":"PlayaPapagayo","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"7620407286","FullDateString":"11 Apr 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What happens when water moves too slowly to notice? In Everglades National Park, it shapes everything. Covering more than 2,300 square miles, the park was established in 1947 to protect a wetland system unlike any other in the United States. As a recognised UNESCO World Heritage Site, the park's elevated pinelands rise above the marshes and prairies that form one of the world's largest wetland systems.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-GB4733846763_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-GB4733846763_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of taking it slow","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.400611,-80.658833/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.400611,-80.658833;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Everglades+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260423_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"4733846763","FullDateString":"24 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every country has a hero. England has one who fought a dragon, carried a red cross and wasn't even English. Meet Saint George—a legend that proves good stories have great travel plans. Celebrated on 23 April, Saint George's Day honours courage and conviction. Though often shown as a gleaming knight, George was a Roman soldier martyred for refusing to give up his faith. The dragon? A later add-on—because history is good, but dragons make it legendary.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.StGeorgeDay2026_EN-GB4338835487_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.StGeorgeDay2026_EN-GB4338835487_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Faith, fire and folklore","Title":"Windsor Castle, Berkshire, England","Copyright":"© Mistervlad/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/51.483887,-0.604393/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=51.483887,-0.604393;S9;Windsor Castle, Berkshire, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260423_StGeorgeDay2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Saint+Georges+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260423_StGeorgeDay2026"},"Ssd":"20260423","Name":"StGeorgeDay2026","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"4338835487","FullDateString":"23 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Earth Day didn't knock gently. It kicked the door wide open. In 1970, oil‑soaked beaches, burning rivers and toxic air mobilised millions into street protests. When looking away was no longer an option, conservation was forced onto political agendas, sparking landmark environmental laws and flipping planet‑care from fringe concern to global priority. Every 22 April, over 190 countries pause, reflect and reassess.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-GB3828067814_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-GB3828067814_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of protest","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/58.466962,26.199884/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=58.466962,26.199884;S9;Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve, Tartu County, Estonia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Earth+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260421_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia"},"Ssd":"20260422","Name":"TartuEstonia","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"3828067814","FullDateString":"22 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-GB3383384255_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-GB3383384255_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spring's prickly patrol","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Its 5,000-7,000 spines are stiff, hollow hairs made of keratin, not true quills like a porcupine's.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"3383384255","FullDateString":"21 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"There are more than 400 sites across the National Park System in the United States that preserve natural and cultural heritage while creating unforgettable outdoor experiences. From coastlines and forests to vast desert landscapes, these protected sites invite exploration, reflection and wonder.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-GB3079917136_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-GB3079917136_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The adventure doesn't end at sundown","Title":"Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.213604,-109.902534/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.213604,-109.902534;S9;Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canyonlands+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"3079917136","FullDateString":"20 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image shows Anne Hathaway's cottage in Stratford‑upon‑Avon, England, the childhood home of Shakespeare's future wife. This 15th-century thatched cottage, now preserved as a museum, offers a rare glimpse into the domestic world that surrounded the young playwright.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-GB5798947669_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-GB5798947669_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"A cottage full of stories","Title":"Anne Hathaway's cottage and garden, Stratford-upon-Avon, England","Copyright":"© David Steele/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.190984,-1.732059/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.190984,-1.732059;S9;Anne Hathaway's cottage, Stratford-upon-Avon, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_HathawayCottage\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Anne+Hathaway+cottage&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_HathawayCottage"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"HathawayCottage","Market":"EN-GB","Hash":"5798947669","FullDateString":"19 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, on World Heritage Day, attention turns to places that tell humanity's shared story—protected for their exceptional cultural or natural value. One of them rises from volcanic stone on Easter Island, Chile. At Rano Raraku, the slopes of an extinct volcano became the workshop where nearly all of the island's famous moai were carved. The image captures this remarkable quarry, where half-finished figures emerge from the rock, frozen mid-creation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-GB2286908744_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-GB2286908744_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The silence of unfinished giants","Title":"Moai statue quarry, Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-27.127001,-109.292099/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-GB&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-27.127001,-109.292099;S9;Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Heritage+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_2300\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId